<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\companions\companion_aloth_quest_2</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>107</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Great and terrible things are at work, [Player Name]. And once again, you seem to be in the middle of it."

Aloth is twisting the edge of his sash between his hands, a purposeful frown on his face.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I promised to tell you what I was doing among the animancers at Port Maje."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"As you may have guessed, I was observing them. Gathering information on the various animancy operation in the region."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I wish I had your clarity."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>He sighs through his nose, his lips pressed together.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What for?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I thought you were looking for a particular Leaden Key group."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Animancy is a subject of particular interest to the Leaden Key. Through it, I hoped to pick up their trail." A spark of pleasure gleams in his eye. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yes, and how better to draw them out?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And then?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's smart."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Seems like a pretty vague plan."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>"After that incident in Old Vailia, I thought more about the Leaden Key and its particular composition."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Go on."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Mostly lunatics in robes, as I recall."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It's existed for over two thousand years. Say what you will about its motives and methods, but that's an impressive tenure."

He clasps his hands behind his back and begins pacing.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Oh, very funny." He gives you a sidelong glance, but the corners of his mouth turn up despite it.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's when I realized how short-sighted I'd been. To think I could change the Leaden Key without understanding how it works."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's when I realized how short-sighted I'd been. To think I could undo the Leaden Key without understanding how it works."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>Iselmyr cackles gleefully as Aloth's thoughtful expression dissolves.

After a moment, she fades away once more.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If you two are finished..." He gives you a sidelong glance, but the corners of his mouth turn up despite it.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I found references to an ancient Leaden Key cabal in the Deadfire. Possibly one of the oldest, if accounts are credible."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And they appear to have been working independently - without direct intervention from Thaos - for almost two millennia." He watches you eagerly, waiting for that to sink in.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You think that by observing them, you can learn how the Leaden Key works."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And how to reform it. Yes."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And how to destroy it. Yes."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Very well. How do we find them?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So they're old. What does it matter?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Most sources refer to them as the 'Painted Masks.' But I haven't met anyone here who knows that name."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>"There's the challenge." He stops pacing.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't know where in the Deadfire they are, exactly. But I was hoping we could look for them together." He folds his hands, looking hopeful and a little sheepish.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'll help as best I can."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Don't worry, Aloth. I promise we'll find them, one way or another."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I believe you." He smiles, but worry crinkles the corners of his eyes.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't want to promise the impossible. There's not much to go on, but we'll try."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's all I ask, [Player Name]." He bows his head.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I understand. I only hope that if we run across them, you'll allow me to investigate." He bows his head.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Find an ancient Leaden Key sect somewhere in a monster-ridden archipelago. Sure, easy."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>52</ID>
      <DefaultText>He chuckles. "For the Watcher who survived the wrath of the gods, I would hope so."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's where it gets complicated." He purses his lips.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>54</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Merely a first step." Still, his ears redden.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>55</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Don't you see? If I understood how they've continued to operate, I could learn how to reform the Leaden Key."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>56</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Don't you see? If I understood how they've persisted, I could learn how to destroy the Leaden Key."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText>As you near a post with a curious symbol painted onto it, Aloth lays a hand on your arm to stop you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>58</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Very well."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>59</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Couldn't we do this later?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>60</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Don't worry, I already know you're working for the Leaden Key."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>62</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Don't tell me you're working for another secret organization..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>63</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't have time for this."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>64</ID>
      <DefaultText>"This is about the reason I came to Deadfire. The people I've been searching for." He looks meaningfully from you back to the Engwithan tower.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>65</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm afraid not." He looks meaningfully from you back to the painted post and the Engwithan tower.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>66</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I now know better than to keep secrets from a man who can read souls." He smiles, but it's strained.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>"I now know better than to keep secrets from a woman who can read souls." He smiles, but it's strained.</FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>67</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I wouldn't insist if it weren't important."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>68</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Oh, very funny." He smiles, but it's strained.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>69</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've made some missteps over the last few years. As a result, I've thought more about the Leaden Key's composition."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>70</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Wahaki of Ori o Koīki paint their faces."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>71</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Actually, I may know who they are. Long ago, Thaos visited a Wahaki chieftain."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>73</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't understand. What did you find?" Trepidation creeps into his expression.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>74</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Truly? Then perhaps we'll find something there." Hope sparks in his blue eyes as he looks to you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>75</ID>
      <DefaultText>Then, his gaze turns back to the ruined Engwithan tower. And the canoes beside it.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>76</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Please, let's look around."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>77</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What exactly have we set in motion, Watcher?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>79</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Rauataians we passed will doubtless spread word of what you've done in Hasongo."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>81</ID>
      <DefaultText>"But others will want to know what you've seen, [Player Name].

"They'll look to you for answers." He watches you uncertainly, his brow furrowed.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>83</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I have to report truthfully."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>85</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'll tell them what they need to hear."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>86</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm worried about what that will lead to."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>87</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What I say makes no difference."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>88</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Don't you worry what will come next? What events you might move forward?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>89</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What is this really about, Aloth?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>90</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If I thought about it that much, I'd never do anything."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>91</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What someone else does with my words is on them, not me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>92</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Of course. That's why I choose my words carefully."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>93</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I doubt my response will mean anything irrevocable."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>94</ID>
      <DefaultText>"This is no small matter." He pinches the bridge of his nose.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>95</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You make it sound so simple." He spreads his hands in exasperation.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>96</ID>
      <DefaultText>"As am I." His frown deepens.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>97</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You heard Eothas himself reveal his plan to end the cycle of reincarnation." He speaks through gritted teeth, looking around as if afraid someone will overhear.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>98</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Now, the rest of the Deadfire will want to know what happened in Magran's Teeth."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>99</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't have any."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>100</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I know. That worries me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>101</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I can sympathize." He gives you a sad half-smile.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>102</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Well. At least I'm not alone in this." He smiles ruefully.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>103</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It reminds me of the question that drew me to the Deadfire.

"The one I've been avoiding." He rubs the back of his neck.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>104</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So you were spying on your friends."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>105</ID>
      <DefaultText>He winces. "Not out of malice. There was simply no better way."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>106</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Listen.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>107</ID>
      <DefaultText>"How the Leaden Key works? How would you learn about that?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>108</ID>
      <DefaultText>"By studying its origins, of course." He pauses long enough to show you a triumphant flash of teeth.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>110</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Fye, dinnae spur the lad."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>112</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We've got more pressing matters. I can't make a detour for this."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>113</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We'll go."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>114</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If there's time."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>115</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's all I ask, [Player Name]." He bows his head.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>116</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Thank you, [Player Name]." He smiles warmly, but there's a hint of trepidation in his expression.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>117</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't know how you can be so certain."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>118</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I still don't understand how you can truly know what they will mean."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>119</ID>
      <DefaultText>"This is a prudent time for me to explain something." He licks his lips, considering his next words. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>120</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Whoever lives here, they've obviously been here a very long time."

He looks at the post with its strangely-painted symbol.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>121</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Anyway, it's late. I suppose that's enough from me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>122</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Anyway, there's daylight yet. I suppose that's enough from me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>123</ID>
      <DefaultText>"These are Wahaki lands, I say. That symbol is a warning to outsiders." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>124</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Hope you got a while. 'Cause I got lots to say about their motives and methods."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>126</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And that looks strangely like the Leaden Key insignia. But... twisted somehow." He cocks his head as if to examine it from another angle.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>127</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm sure. But imagine what we could learn from them." 

He turns back to you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>128</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Relax, Edér. I'm not defending them."

He turns back to you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
